OL,3,CAurigny CEO defends Guernsey's airline
OL,4,Csaying it's faring better than others
OL,6,FHundreds of islanders attended an IOD
OL,7,Fevent this morning (Friday 27
OL,8,FSeptember), to explore the future of
OL,9,FGuernsey's air connections.
OL,11,FNico Bezuidenhout, CEO of Aurigny,
OL,12,Fmade his first appearance after a
OL,13,Fstrained month for the airline.
OL,15,FHe appeared alongside Peter Roffey,
OL,16,Fthe Deputy responsible for overseeing
OL,17,FGuernsey's airline.
OL,19,FAurigny has struggled with tech issues
OL,20,Fleading to numerous delays and
OL,21,Fcancellations.
