OL,3,CAurigny CEO defends Guernsey's airline
OL,4,Csaying it's faring better than others
OL,6,FNico Beizendehout admitted that 2024
OL,7,Fhad been a "misery" for the airline.
OL,9,FHowever, in response to public and
OL,10,Findustry concern, the packed audience
OL,11,Fwere told by an aviation consultant
OL,12,Fthat Guernsey is actually doing better
OL,13,Fthan most airlines.
OL,15,FThe audience were told that Guernsey
OL,16,Fis lucky to have Aurigny and that the
OL,17,Fisland is punching above its weight
OL,18,Fcompared to similar small airports.
